name: dfs.datanode.data.transfer.bandwidthPerSec
description:
Specifies the maximum amount of bandwidth that the data transfering can utilize for transfering block when
      BlockConstructionStage is
      PIPELINE_SETUP_CREATE and clientName is empty.
      When the bandwidth value is zero, there is no limit.

name: mapreduce.job.speculative.retry-after-no-speculate
description:
The waiting time(ms) to do next round of speculation
  if there is no task speculated in this round.

name: dfs.namenode.read-lock-reporting-threshold-ms
description:
When a read lock is held on the namenode for a long time,
    this will be logged as the lock is released. This sets how long the
    lock must be held for logging to occur.

name: hadoop.security.groups.cache.background.reload.threads
description:
Only relevant if hadoop.security.groups.cache.background.reload is true.
    Controls the number of concurrent background user->group cache entry
    refreshes. Pending refresh requests beyond this value are queued and
    processed when a thread is free.

name: dfs.datanode.restart.replica.expiration
description:
During shutdown for restart, the amount of time in seconds budgeted for
    datanode restart.

name: yarn.app.mapreduce.client-am.ipc.max-retries-on-timeouts
description:
The number of client retries on socket timeouts to the AM - before
    reconnecting to the RM to fetch Application Status.
    In other words, it is the ipc.client.connect.max.retries.on.timeouts to be used during
    reconnecting to the RM and fetching Application Status.

name: hadoop.http.idle_timeout.ms
description: NN/JN/DN Server connection timeout in milliseconds.

name: mapreduce.job.encrypted-intermediate-data-key-size-bits
description: Mapreduce encrypt data key size default is 128
